frameDefinitions: This frame is concerned with the idea that people (Participant_1, Participant_2, or Participants) participate in an organized, rule-governed activity (the Competition) in order to achieve some advantageous outcome (often the Prize).
An Entity aids in the successful completion of a Purpose.
An Experiencer has a greater desire to participate in some Event, as against another (contextually recoverable) event which exhibits a specific Contrast with the Event.
Money is a medium used for exchanging goods and services.
A Benefactor confers a Beneficial_situation to a Beneficiary.
An Experiencer is in an undesirable Situation, whose Explanation may also be expressed.
frameExamples: A box is an <t>ideal</t> storage device.
The <t>money</t> for our daughter's college education is currently earning interest in a savings account.
His presence at the summit did not <t>BENEFIT</t> diplomatic relations in the slightest.
The insurers ended up in the <t>bind</t> of having to pay 15 years' taxes.
listRoleDefinitions: This role identifies the first (or only) participant in a competition.
This role identifies the second participant in a competition.
This role is used for plural NP participants in a competition.
This role is used for the name of the competition.
The period of time when the <fen>Competition</fen> occurs.

Where the event takes place. 
A constituent tagged as <fen>Place</fen> may require annotation on a secondary FE-layer.
The item which is useful for some purpose.
The kind of task which is promoted by the use or presence of the <fen>Entity</fen>.
When the <fen>Entity</fen> is useful for a <fen>Purpose</fen>.
The <fen>Experiencer</fen> is the person (or sentient being) who wishes for the <fen>Event</fen> to occur.
The change that the <fen>Experiencer</fen> would like to see.
This is the entity that the <fen>Experiencer</fen> wishes to be affected by some <fen>Event</fen>.
The <fen>Location_of_event</fen> is the place involved in the desired <fen>Event</fen>.
An alternative <fen>Event</fen> or <fen>Focal_participant</fen> that is less desirable for the <fen>Experiencer</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the <fen>Experiencer</fen> desires something.
Where the event takes place.  Note that this role is of extremely rare occurrence in this frame.
<fen>Money</fen> is used as a medium of exchange.
The <fen>Benefactor</fen> is the person or thing that gives an advantage to the <fen>Beneficiary</fen>.
The <fen>Beneficiary</fen> is person or thing that receives an advantage from the <fen>Benefactor</fen>.

The <fen>Beneficial_situation</fen> is the item or action that is given to or done for the <fen>Beneficiary</fen> by the <fen>Benefactor</fen>.  A change of possession can, but does not have to occur.
The <fen>Experiencer</fen> is in an undesirable <fen>Situation</fen>.
This role identifies the undesirable <fen>Situation</fen> the <fen>Experiencer</fen> is in.
Thiis role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Situation</fen> is in effect.
The location where the <fen>Situation</fen> occurs.
listRoleExamples: First layer: John's first competition <fex>at Wimbledon</fex> astonished the crowd.
<fex>The insurers</fex> ended up in a bind.
They found themselves in a quite <fex>a fix</fex>.
<fex>Yesterday's</fex> predicament was a little too exciting.
The trouble <fex>in America</fex> is only going to get worse.
